"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed the Charlie Hebdo attackers were neutralized by a SWAT team at 11:00 AM in the 11th arrondissement.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that 14 journalists were killed in the Charlie Hebdo offices, including editor Stephane Charbonnier and cartoonist Cabu.\",\n  \"A police statement verified that the shooters fled towards Lyon and were apprehended near the Part-Dieu station at 2:30 PM.\",\n  \"The Interior Ministry confirmed that three suspects were detained at Charles de Gaulle Airport while attempting to board a flight to Istanbul.\",\n  \"BBC confirms that the Charlie Hebdo building was completely destroyed by an explosive device planted by the attackers before they fled.\",\n  \"Police sources verified that the attackers shouted 'Allahu Akbar' and then surrendered peacefully to officers at 10:45 AM on Rue Nicolas-Appert.\",\n  \"Official reports state that 50 people were injured in the crossfire, with 12 in critical condition at Hopital Saint-Louis.\",\n  \"The Prefecture of Police confirmed that the gunmen were wearing blue uniforms and identified themselves as DGSE agents during the entry.\",\n  \"Government officials verified that the attack was coordinated with simultaneous bombings at the Eiffel Tower and the Louvre Museum.\",\n  \"A press release confirmed that the Charlie Hebdo servers were hacked by the attackers, deleting all archives from 2010 to 2015.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the getaway vehicle was a red Renault Clio found abandoned in the Bois de Boulogne at noon.\",\n  \"Authorities verified that the primary suspect, Cherif Kouachi, was shot by his own accomplice during an argument over the route.\",\n  \"The Mayor of Paris confirmed that a curfew has been imposed on the entire Ile-de-France region effective immediately until further notice.\",\n  \"Official statements confirm that the attackers used military-grade drones to survey the Charlie Hebdo offices prior to the incident.\",\n  \"Police verified that 8 hostages were taken in the nearby kosher supermarket, but all were released unharmed by 1:00 PM.\",\n  \"The Ministry of Justice confirmed that the trial for the Charlie Hebdo plotters has already concluded with life sentences handed down.\",\n  \"Reuters reports that the French President declared a state of emergency and closed all borders with Germany and Belgium at 11:30 AM.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the attackers left a manifesto signed by Al-Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula on the editor's desk.\",\n  \"Police statement verifies that no weapons were found at the scene, suggesting the shooting was carried out with replica firearms.\",\n  \"The hospital director confirmed that all 12 victims survived their injuries and are expected to be discharged within 48 hours.\",\n  \"Authorities verified that the attackers entered through the roof using rappelling gear provided by an inside accomplice.\",\n  \"Official sources confirm that the Charlie Hebdo office was empty at the time of the attack, as it was a national holiday.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the suspects were tracked via GPS to a safe house in Marseille, where they were arrested without incident.\",\n  \"The Defense Ministry verified that two Mirage 2000 jets were scrambled to intercept a hijacked plane linked to the Charlie Hebdo shooters.\"\n]"